Kyorl'jabbuk of<BR><a href="http://members.tripod.com/selquar">House Sel'Quar</a></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ubladeofevil.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Blade of Evil</A> at: 1/17/02 12:46:25 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ublakkon.showPublicProfile?language=EN>blakkon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 43<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/17/02 12:49:05 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1137.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A crisis of faith (long)</span><hr size=1> Marrik, I also wrestle with the alignment of the gods and their followers in Norrath, though I focus more on the interaction of order and discord.  I see the same petty bigotries, the same arrogance, the same narrowmindedness in all who focus their lives on good/evil.  They fail to see they are much the same and that the true battle is that of order vs chaos....  In your travels feel free to seek me out.  In my quest for balance I have so far learned to speak the Dark elven tongue and am working on Elvish, also I speak well  my native Northman and the more common Human.<br>
<br>
To others,  while it is true that many individual Dark Elves follow discord, the entire structure of their society is based on the rule of law.  In this sense they are much like the High elves.  If you compare the two, you see the same great achievements in architecture, society, and the mastery of the intellectual and religious arts, these are hallmarks of an orderly society.  A more appropriate opposing force to the Tier'dal is found in the wood elves.  While Dark elf society is Evil and ordered, the wood elves are disorderly and good. <p>Lorec <br>
